HappyPlant Firmware
===================

ESP8266 (NodeMCU v2) environmental monitor that reads temperature and humidity
from an HTU21D sensor, displays readings on an OLED, and logs data to InfluxDB.

Setup
-----

1. Create a secrets file at `include/secrets.h` with your WiFi credentials:

   #ifndef SECRETS_H
   #define SECRETS_H

   const char* ssid     = "YOUR_WIFI_SSID";
   const char* password = "YOUR_WIFI_PASSWORD";

   #endif

   This file is gitignored and will not be committed.

2. Update `include/config.h` to set your display size, device ID, and server IP.

3. Update `include/influxDbConfig.h` with your InfluxDB URL and token.

4. Flash with PlatformIO:

   pio run --target upload
